{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1202,"text":"Scientific breakthrough,"},{"time":2711,"text":"the kind that can potentially save lives,"},{"time":5324,"text":"can sometimes be lying right out in the open"},{"time":7388,"text":"for us to discover,"},{"time":8950,"text":"in the evolved, accumulated body"},{"time":11156,"text":"of human anecdote, for example,"},{"time":13748,"text":"or in the time-tested adaptations"},{"time":15774,"text":"that we observe in the natural world around us."},{"time":19236,"text":"Science starts with observation,"},{"time":21856,"text":"but the trick is to identify the patterns and signatures"},{"time":25252,"text":"that we might otherwise dismiss"},{"time":27197,"text":"as myth or coincidence,"},{"time":29064,"text":"isolate them, and test them with scientific rigor."},{"time":32917,"text":"And when we do, the results will often surprise."}]},{"cues":[{"time":36975,"text":"Western Australia has had a particular problem"},{"time":38855,"text":"with shark attacks over the last three years,"},{"time":42070,"text":"unfortunately and tragically culminating"},{"time":44251,"text":"in five fatal shark attacks in a 10-month period"},{"time":47331,"text":"during that time."},{"time":49091,"text":"But Western Australia is not alone in this."},{"time":51220,"text":"The incident of shark engagements on humans"},{"time":54125,"text":"is escalating worldwide."},{"time":56469,"text":"And so it's not surprising, perhaps,"},{"time":58213,"text":"that in July of this year,"},{"time":59856,"text":"Shark Attack Mitigation Systems in collaboration"},{"time":62335,"text":"with the University of Western\nAustralia Oceans Institute"},{"time":65399,"text":"made an announcement which captured the attention"},{"time":68173,"text":"of the worldwide media and of ocean users"},{"time":70409,"text":"worldwide,"},{"time":72200,"text":"and that was around the development of technology"},{"time":73931,"text":"to mitigate or reduce the risk of shark attack"},{"time":76572,"text":"based on the science of what sharks can see."},{"time":79720,"text":"And I have for you today"},{"time":81309,"text":"the story of that journey,"},{"time":83176,"text":"but also the notion that science can be"},{"time":85516,"text":"as powerful as a translator"},{"time":87981,"text":"as it can be for invention."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91340,"text":"When we began this process,"},{"time":93046,"text":"we were looking, it was about three years ago,"},{"time":96228,"text":"and we'd just had the first two fatal shark attacks"},{"time":99650,"text":"in Western Australia,"},{"time":101421,"text":"and by chance, in a previous role,"},{"time":103628,"text":"I happened to be having dinner with Harry Butler."},{"time":106551,"text":"Now Harry Butler, who most Australians\nwould know is a famous naturalist,"},{"time":110258,"text":"had spent a lot of time in the marine environment."},{"time":112593,"text":"Harry Butler is a precursor, if you like,"},{"time":114699,"text":"to the late Steve Irwin."},{"time":116610,"text":"When I asked him about"},{"time":117921,"text":"what the solution to the problem might be,"},{"time":121219,"text":"the answer was quite surprising."},{"time":122731,"text":"He said, \"Take a black wetsuit,"},{"time":124606,"text":"band it in yellow stripes like a bumblebee,"},{"time":127371,"text":"and you'll be mimicking the warning systems"},{"time":129659,"text":"of most marine species.\""},{"time":131968,"text":"I didn't think about that much at the time,"},{"time":133866,"text":"and it wasn't until the next three\nfatal shark attacks happened,"},{"time":137456,"text":"and it caused me to think,"},{"time":138890,"text":"maybe there's some merit to this idea."},{"time":141021,"text":"And I turned to the web"},{"time":142486,"text":"to see if there might be some clues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144741,"text":"And it turns out the web is awash"},{"time":147018,"text":"with this sort of evidence that supports"},{"time":149414,"text":"this sort of thinking."},{"time":150976,"text":"So biologically, there are plenty of species"},{"time":152960,"text":"that display banding or patterns, warning patterns,"},{"time":155556,"text":"to either be cryptical in the water"},{"time":157258,"text":"or warn against being attacked,"},{"time":159842,"text":"not the least of which is the pilot fish"},{"time":161955,"text":"which spends a big slab of its life"},{"time":164111,"text":"around the business end of a shark."},{"time":166390,"text":"On the human side, Walter Starck, an oceanographer,"},{"time":169481,"text":"has been painting his wetsuit since the 1970s,"},{"time":172343,"text":"and anthropologically,"},{"time":173965,"text":"Pacific island tribes painted themselves in bands"},{"time":177595,"text":"in a sea snake ceremony"},{"time":179376,"text":"to ward off the shark god."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181970,"text":"So what's going on here?"},{"time":183412,"text":"Is this an idea lying wide out in the open"},{"time":186290,"text":"for us to consider and define?"},{"time":189421,"text":"We know that sharks use a range of sensors"},{"time":193790,"text":"when they engage, particularly for attack,"},{"time":197162,"text":"but the sight sensor is the one that they use"},{"time":199122,"text":"to identify the target, and particularly"},{"time":200686,"text":"in the last number of meters before the attack."},{"time":204420,"text":"It makes sense to pay attention\nto the biological anecdote"},{"time":207378,"text":"because that's time-tested evolution"},{"time":209230,"text":"over many millennia."},{"time":211703,"text":"But isn't human anecdote also an evolution of sorts,"},{"time":215180,"text":"the idea that there's a kernel of truth"},{"time":216911,"text":"thought to be important,"},{"time":218503,"text":"passed down from generation to generation,"},{"time":221788,"text":"so that it actually ends up shaping human behavior?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":225103,"text":"I wanted to test this idea."},{"time":226763,"text":"I wanted to put some science"},{"time":227981,"text":"to this anecdotal evidence,"},{"time":230317,"text":"because if science could support this concept,"},{"time":232273,"text":"then we might have at least part of the solution"},{"time":234368,"text":"to shark attack right under our very nose."},{"time":237426,"text":"To do that, I needed some experts"},{"time":239221,"text":"in shark vision and shark neurology,"},{"time":241074,"text":"and a worldwide search, again,"},{"time":242883,"text":"led to the University of W.A."},{"time":244322,"text":"on the doorstep here, with the Oceans Institute."},{"time":246725,"text":"And professor Nathan Hart and his team"},{"time":249322,"text":"had just written a paper which tells us,"},{"time":251982,"text":"confirms that predatory sharks see"},{"time":254334,"text":"in black and white, or grayscale."},{"time":257197,"text":"So I called up Nathan,"},{"time":259000,"text":"a little bit sheepishly, actually, about this idea"},{"time":260866,"text":"that maybe we could use these patterns and shapes"},{"time":262747,"text":"to produce a wetsuit to try and\nmitigate the risk of shark attack,"},{"time":266253,"text":"and fortunately, he thought that was a good idea."},{"time":268425,"text":"So what ensued is a collaborative bit of research"},{"time":270887,"text":"supported by the West Australian State Government."},{"time":273511,"text":"And we did three key things."},{"time":276070,"text":"The first is that we mapped the characteristics,"},{"time":278790,"text":"the physical characteristics of the eyes"},{"time":280810,"text":"of the three main predatory sharks,"},{"time":282748,"text":"so the great white, tiger and bull shark."},{"time":286466,"text":"We did that genetically"},{"time":288020,"text":"and we did that anatomically."},{"time":290920,"text":"The next thing we did was to understand,"},{"time":292762,"text":"using complex computer modeling,"},{"time":294197,"text":"what that eye can see"},{"time":296251,"text":"at different depths, distances,"},{"time":298020,"text":"light conditions, and water clarity in the ocean."},{"time":302261,"text":"And from there, we were able to pinpoint"},{"time":303451,"text":"two key characteristics:"},{"time":305251,"text":"what patterns and shapes would present the wearer"},{"time":308284,"text":"as hidden or hard to make out in the water, cryptic,"},{"time":311516,"text":"and what patterns and shapes might provide"},{"time":313012,"text":"the greatest contrast but provide the greatest"},{"time":315933,"text":"breakup of profile"},{"time":317390,"text":"so that that person wasn't confused for shark prey"},{"time":321034,"text":"or shark food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323387,"text":"The next thing we needed to do was to convert this"},{"time":325579,"text":"into wetsuits that people might actually wear,"},{"time":328328,"text":"and to that end, I invited Ray Smith,"},{"time":330950,"text":"a surfer, industrial designer, wetsuit designer,"},{"time":334180,"text":"and in fact the guy that designed\nthe original Quiksilver logo,"},{"time":336542,"text":"to come over and sit with the science team"},{"time":338827,"text":"and interpret that science"},{"time":342423,"text":"into aesthetic wetsuits that\npeople might actually wear."},{"time":345565,"text":"And here's an example of one of the first drawings."},{"time":348021,"text":"So this is what I call a \"don't eat me\" wetsuit."},{"time":351025,"text":"So this takes that banding idea,"},{"time":355294,"text":"takes that banding idea, it's highly visible,"},{"time":357880,"text":"provides a highly disruptive profile,"},{"time":359885,"text":"and is intended to prevent the shark"},{"time":361712,"text":"from considering that you would be ordinary food,"},{"time":364380,"text":"and potentially even create confusion for the shark."},{"time":367726,"text":"And this one's configured to go with a surfboard."},{"time":371501,"text":"You can see that dark, opaque panel on the front,"},{"time":374114,"text":"and it's particularly better for the surface,"},{"time":376841,"text":"where being backlit and providing a silhouette"},{"time":379689,"text":"is problematic."},{"time":381301,"text":"Second iteration is the cryptic wetsuit,"},{"time":384209,"text":"or the one which attempts to hide the wearer"},{"time":385820,"text":"in the water column."},{"time":387310,"text":"There are three panels on this suit,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and in any given conditions,"},{"time":390624,"text":"one or more of those panels"},{"time":391979,"text":"will match the reflective spectra of the water"},{"time":394569,"text":"so as to disappear fully or partially,"},{"time":397168,"text":"leaving the last panel or panels"},{"time":399360,"text":"to create a disruptive profile in the water column."},{"time":402247,"text":"And this one's particularly well-suited"},{"time":404412,"text":"to the dive configuration,"},{"time":406859,"text":"so when you're deeper under the water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409927,"text":"So we knew that we had"},{"time":411637,"text":"some really solid science here."},{"time":413407,"text":"We knew, if you wanted to stand out,"},{"time":415033,"text":"you needed to look stripy,"},{"time":416205,"text":"and we knew if you wanted to be cryptic,"},{"time":417629,"text":"you needed to look like this."},{"time":419181,"text":"But the acid test is always going to be,"},{"time":421007,"text":"how would sharks really behave"},{"time":422339,"text":"in the context of these patterns and shapes."},{"time":425070,"text":"And testing to simulate a person in a wetsuit"},{"time":428381,"text":"in the water with a predatory shark"},{"time":429929,"text":"in a natural environment"},{"time":431295,"text":"is actually a lot harder than you might think."},{"time":433247,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":436598,"text":"So we have to bait the rig,"},{"time":439164,"text":"because we need to get the statistical number"},{"time":440708,"text":"of samples through to get the scientific evidence,"},{"time":443732,"text":"and by baiting the rig,"},{"time":444521,"text":"we're obviously changing shark behavior."},{"time":446750,"text":"We can't put humans in the water."},{"time":448567,"text":"We're ethically precluded from even using"},{"time":451453,"text":"humanoid shapes and baiting them up in the water."},{"time":454100,"text":"But nevertheless, we started the testing process"},{"time":456372,"text":"in January of this year,"},{"time":458220,"text":"initially with tiger sharks"},{"time":459356,"text":"and subsequently with great white sharks."},{"time":462695,"text":"The way we did that"},{"time":464130,"text":"was to get a perforated drum which is full of bait,"},{"time":468885,"text":"wrap it in a neoprene skin,"},{"time":470781,"text":"and then run two stereo underwater cameras"},{"time":473344,"text":"to watch how the shark\nactually engages with that rig."},{"time":476693,"text":"And because we use stereo,"},{"time":478381,"text":"we can capture all the statistics\non how big the shark is,"},{"time":481173,"text":"what angle it comes in at, how quickly it leaves,"},{"time":483429,"text":"and what its behavior is"},{"time":485285,"text":"in an empirical rather than a subjective way."},{"time":488491,"text":"Because we needed to\npreserve the scientific method,"},{"time":490979,"text":"we ran a control rig"},{"time":492677,"text":"which was a black neoprene rig"},{"time":496389,"text":"just like a normal black wetsuit"},{"time":498198,"text":"against the, what we call,"},{"time":499677,"text":"SAMS technology rig."},{"time":501805,"text":"And the results were not just exciting,"},{"time":504533,"text":"but very encouraging,"},{"time":505971,"text":"and today I would like to just give you a snapshot"},{"time":508519,"text":"of two of those engagements."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512181,"text":"So here we've got a four-meter tiger shark"},{"time":514301,"text":"engaging the black control rig,"},{"time":517388,"text":"which it had encountered about"},{"time":518729,"text":"a minute and a half before."},{"time":539780,"text":"Now that exact same shark had engaged,"},{"time":542210,"text":"or encountered this SAMS rig,"},{"time":544040,"text":"which is the Elude SAMS rig,"},{"time":545652,"text":"about eight minutes before,"},{"time":546831,"text":"and spent six minutes circling it, hunting for it,"},{"time":549974,"text":"looking for what it could\nsmell and sense but not see,"},{"time":552779,"text":"and this was the final engagement."},{"time":557734,"text":"Great white sharks are more\nconfident than the tigers,"},{"time":560687,"text":"and here you see great white shark"},{"time":562735,"text":"engaging a control rig,"},{"time":564142,"text":"so a black neoprene wetsuit,"},{"time":565975,"text":"and going straight to the bottom,"},{"time":567559,"text":"coming up"},{"time":570110,"text":"and engaging."},{"time":574257,"text":"In contrast to the SAMS technology rig,"},{"time":576940,"text":"this is the banded one,"},{"time":578409,"text":"where it's more tactile,"},{"time":580350,"text":"it's more investigative,"},{"time":581860,"text":"it's more apprehensive,"},{"time":583494,"text":"and shows a reluctance to come straight in and go."},{"time":596297,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":606601,"text":"So, it's important for us that all \nthe testing is done independently,"},{"time":610877,"text":"and the University of W.A. is doing the testing."},{"time":613195,"text":"It'll be an ongoing process."},{"time":614947,"text":"It's subject to peer review and subject to publication."},{"time":617356,"text":"It's so important that this concept"},{"time":619699,"text":"is led with the science."},{"time":621497,"text":"From the perspective of Shark \nAttack Mitigation Systems,"},{"time":623741,"text":"we're a biotechnology licensing company,"},{"time":626146,"text":"so we don't make wetsuits ourselves."},{"time":628433,"text":"We'll license others to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630713,"text":"But I thought you might be interested"},{"time":631672,"text":"in seeing what SAMS technology looks like"},{"time":633673,"text":"embedded in a wetsuit, and to that end,"},{"time":636672,"text":"for the first time, live, worldwide --"},{"time":639888,"text":"(Laughter) â€”"},{"time":641862,"text":"I can show you what biological adaptation,"},{"time":644758,"text":"science and design looks like in real life."},{"time":648285,"text":"So I can welcome Sam, the surfer,"},{"time":650182,"text":"from this side. Where are you, Sam?"},{"time":652890,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":654686,"text":"And Eduardo."},{"time":656356,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":658172,"text":"Cheers, mate."},{"time":660866,"text":"Cheers."},{"time":662956,"text":"Thanks, gentlemen. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":669656,"text":"So what have we done here?"},{"time":670943,"text":"Well, to my mind, rather than take a blank sheet"},{"time":673960,"text":"and use science as a tool for invention,"},{"time":677280,"text":"we've paid attention to the biological evidence,"},{"time":680136,"text":"we've put importance to the"},{"time":681826,"text":"human anecdotal evidence,"},{"time":683536,"text":"and we've used science as a tool"},{"time":686618,"text":"for translation,"},{"time":688021,"text":"translation of something that was already there"},{"time":690248,"text":"into something that we can \nuse for the benefit of mankind."},{"time":693819,"text":"And it strikes me that this idea of science"},{"time":695743,"text":"as a tool for translation rather than invention"},{"time":698799,"text":"is one that we can apply much more widely than this"},{"time":701463,"text":"in the pursuit of innovation."},{"time":703410,"text":"After all, did the Wright brothers"},{"time":705735,"text":"discover manned flight,"},{"time":707787,"text":"or did they observe the biological fact of flight"},{"time":710976,"text":"and translate that mechanically, replicate it"},{"time":714168,"text":"in a way that humans could use?"},{"time":716685,"text":"As for the humble wetsuit,"},{"time":718219,"text":"who knows what oceanwear will look like"},{"time":720160,"text":"in two years' time, in five years' time"},{"time":723111,"text":"or in 50 years' time, but with this new thinking,"},{"time":726203,"text":"I'm guessing there's a fair chance"},{"time":727469,"text":"it won't be pure black."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729190,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731359,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}